[4] Russia
Date: Wed 6 Dec 2017
Source: Business monkey News [edited]
https://businessmonkeynews.com/en/en/the-cases-of-measles-in-russia-increase-in-four-times-in-2017/


People with measles in Russia increased by 4 times in 10 months of 2017, reported the Department of Protection of Consumer Rights (Rospotrebnadzor).

"Measles cases detected between January and October 2017 increased by 4.3 times compared to the same period last year [2016] to stand at 0.25 per 100 000 people," reads a statement from the entity.

It is noted that in total, in this period, 367 cases of measles were detected, compared to 86 cases in 2016. According to the statement, the largest number of patients was detected in Dagestan, the Chechen Republic, Moscow and its province.

